AgentForce Infotech On-Call Rotation and Procedures

## On-Call Schedule

- Rotation changes every Monday at 9:00 AM IST
- Schedule posted in #agentforce-oncall Slack channel
- Each engineer serves one week per quarter (approximately)
- Backup on-call assigned for coverage (secondary engineer)
- Schedule managed by Vikram Singh (Tech Lead)

Current rotation order: Backend team → Frontend team → DevOps team → QA team

## Responsibilities

1. Monitor alerts and error dashboards (Grafana, PagerDuty, Sentry)
2. Respond to critical incidents within SLA (see severity levels below)
3. Escalate to senior engineers or Tech Lead if needed
4. Document incidents in Jira (project: INCIDENT)
5. Hand off to next on-call engineer (Monday morning standup)

## Alert Severity Levels

**P0 - Critical (Immediate Response - 15 minutes)**
- Production application down (app.agentforce.com unavailable)
- Data breach or security incident
- Payment processing system failure
- Database corruption or data loss
- Response Time: Within 15 minutes
- Escalation: Immediately to Tech Lead (Vikram Singh) and CTO

**P1 - High (Urgent - 1 hour)**
- Major feature broken (affecting >50% users)
- Performance degradation (response time >5 seconds)
- API rate limiting issues
- Critical third-party service outage
- Response Time: Within 1 hour
- Escalation: After 30 minutes if unresolved

**P2 - Medium (Normal - 4 hours)**
- Minor feature issues (affecting <50% users)
- Non-critical errors (logging, monitoring)
- Staging environment issues
- Response Time: Within 4 hours (business hours)

**P3 - Low (Low Priority - Next Business Day)**
- Cosmetic UI issues
- Enhancement requests
- Documentation updates
- Response Time: Next business day

## Tools

- **PagerDuty**: Alert routing and on-call management
  - URL: https://agentforce.pagerduty.com
  - Mobile app required (install on phone)
  
- **Grafana**: Monitoring dashboards
  - URL: https://grafana.agentforce.internal
  - Key dashboards: Production Health, API Latency, Error Rates
  
- **Sentry**: Error tracking and alerting
  - URL: https://sentry.agentforce.internal
  - Alerts for new errors and error spikes
  
- **Status Page**: Outage communication
  - URL: https://status.agentforce.com
  - Update during P0/P1 incidents

## Incident Response Process

1. **Acknowledge** alert in PagerDuty (within 5 minutes)
2. **Assess** severity and impact (check Grafana, Sentry)
3. **Create** incident ticket in Jira (project: INCIDENT)
4. **Investigate** and attempt to fix
5. **Communicate** status in #agentforce-incidents Slack channel
6. **Post-mortem** required for P0/P1 incidents (within 48 hours)

## Escalation Path

If unable to resolve:
- **P0**: Escalate immediately to Tech Lead (Vikram Singh - vikram.singh@agentforce.com, mobile in directory)
- **P1**: Escalate after 30 minutes of investigation to Tech Lead
- **P2/P3**: Document in Jira, handle during business hours

Contact channels:
- #agentforce-incident-response Slack channel
- On-call phone tree (in 1Password: "On-Call Escalation")

## On-Call Compensation

- Additional 2 PTO days per on-call week
- Overtime pay for P0 incidents resolved outside business hours
- Recognition in quarterly all-hands meeting

## Handoff Process

Every Monday 9:00 AM IST:
- Current on-call presents incidents from previous week
- Next on-call receives PagerDuty access and context
- Any ongoing incidents documented in Jira

For questions, contact Vikram Singh (Tech Lead) or check #agentforce-oncall channel.
